      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Commentary: P2714"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P2714",
      "text": "DTC P2714: Lock-up clutch control SOL.V. OFF Stuck"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "147_3.0_jpn_11033690_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The lock-up clutch control SOL.V. controls the hydraulic pressure applied to the lock-up clutch. The spool in the lock-up clutch control SOL.V. pushes a valve in response to the duty (load) output, which is converted to a current value by the PGM-FI ECU. As a result, the valve pushed by the spool releases oil pressure proportional to the current value. The PGM-FI ECU outputs a control signal for the lock-up clutch oil pressure for proper lock-up. If the lock-up clutch remains OFF for a predetermined period of time in the running state, the PGM-FI ECU judges that the lock-up clutch control SOL.V. is stuck OFF and stores the DTC."
    },
